From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000032 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Sat, 5 Jul 2026 02:05:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: omap-usb-host: depopulate DT children on remove

usbhs_omap_remove() unregisters the child devices with
device_for_each_child() but never clears their DT nodes' OF_POPULATED
flags, so after a driver unbind the re-probe's of_platform_populate()
silently skips re-creating the EHCI/OHCI children -- the USB host is
gone until reboot. Call of_platform_depopulate() first (it unregisters
the DT-created children AND clears the flags); keep the child walk for
any non-DT children. Found live on the Nexus Q while attempting a
runtime re-init of the ethernet bring-up.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
@@ -838,7 +838,17 @@
 {
 	pm_runtime_disable(&pdev->dev);
 
-	/* remove children */
+	/*
+	 * Depopulate the DT children properly: device_for_each_child alone
+	 * leaves the child nodes' OF_POPULATED flags set, so a re-probe's
+	 * of_platform_populate() silently skips re-creating the EHCI/OHCI
+	 * child devices and the controller is gone until reboot (hit live
+	 * on the Nexus Q 2026-07-05 while attempting a runtime re-init of
+	 * the ethernet bring-up).
+	 */
+	of_platform_depopulate(&pdev->dev);
+
+	/* remove any remaining non-DT children */
 	device_for_each_child(&pdev->dev, NULL, usbhs_omap_remove_child);
 }
 
